President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key administration posts. Carla A. Harris will be appointed as Chairperson of the National Women's Business Council. She is currently the Vice Chairman of Global Wealth Management at Morgan Stanley. S. Fitzgerald Haney will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. He is currently the Director of Business Development and Client Services at Pzena Investment Management. Beth Heifetz will also be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. She is currently a partner at the law firm Jones Day.